1 An Act to revise a provision related to service of process for boards of county
2 commissioners.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That § 7-8-29 be AMENDED:
5 7-8-29. Such appeal shall be taken within twenty days after the publication of the
6 decision of the board by serving a written notice on one of the members of the board,
7 upon any county administrator, auditor or commissioner, executive, treasurer, or any
8 registered agent of the board upon the state's attorney of that county, or upon any person
9 appointed by the board pursuant to resolution to accept notice, when the appeal is taken
10 by any person aggrieved by the decision of the board, and upon the person or persons
11 affected by the decision of the board when the appeal is taken by the state's attorney;
12 and the county auditor shall upon.
13 Upon the filing of the required bond and the payment of his fees, which shall be
14 the same as allowed registers are equal to those imposed by a register of deeds for like
15 services, the county auditor shall make out a complete transcript of the proceedings of
16 the board relating to the matter of its the board's decision and deliver the same transcript
17 to the clerk of courts.
